{
  "countryId": "france",
  "focuses": [
    {
      "id": "FRA_shinainaru_doushi",
      "col": 4,
      "row": 4,
      "icon": "",
      "name": {
        "ja": "親愛なる我らが導師",
        "en": "Our Beloved Guru"
      },
      "description": {
        "ja": "「崇高なる国」の建国者であり、超現実主義の予言者たるアポリネールの頭部の古傷が悪化し、彼は病床に伏すことが多くなった。全国民が祈りを捧げる中、彼のうわ言すらも信者たちにとっては神聖な啓示として書き留められている。",
        "en": "The old head wound of Apollinaire, the founder of 'La Sublime' and the prophet of surrealism, has worsened, confining him to his sickbed. As the nation prays, even his delirious mutterings are transcribed by his followers as sacred revelations."
      },
      "effects": {
        "events": [
          {
            "id": "FRA_our_guru_event",
            "name": {
              "ja": "我らが導師の紹介！",
              "en": "Introduction of Our Guru!"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "prerequisites": [
        "FRA_suukounaru_kuni_no_makuake"
      ],
      "mutuallyExclusive": []
    },
    {
      "id": "FRA_kuuseki_no_ouza",
      "col": 4,
      "row": 5,
      "icon": "",
      "name": {
        "ja": "空席の王座",
        "en": "Vacancy on the Throne"
      },
      "description": {
        "ja": "1932年、導師はついに肉体を脱ぎ捨て、より高次なる精神世界へと旅立った。パリに残された「空席の王座」を巡り、残された後継者たちは彼の遺した謎めいた詩篇を各々の都合のいいように解釈し、国境を越えた狂気へと国を駆り立てようとしている。",
        "en": "In 1932, the Guru finally shed his physical form to embark on a journey to a higher spiritual realm. Around the 'Vacant Throne' left in Paris, his successors battle for control, each interpreting his cryptic poems to suit their own ambitions, driving the nation towards a madness that transcends borders."
      },
      "effects": {
        "events": [
          {
            "id": "FRA_kuuseki_no_ouza_event",
            "name": {
              "ja": "導師の死",
              "en": "Teacher's Death"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "prerequisites": [
        "FRA_shinainaru_doushi"
      ],
      "mutuallyExclusive": []
    },
